23/05/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The police announced on Saturday (May 22nd) they have arrested five people in Prizren on suspicion of illegal arms possession.
The operation, involving 100 police officers, was carried out in eight sites in the Prizren region.
Two Kosovo Albanians and three Bosniaks who are suspected of links with the Wahhabi movement are among those detained.
Police also seized large amount of weapons during the raids.
(Beta, Tanjug, Radio Free Europe, AP, Reuters - 22/05/10)
